@CR

Welcome to IE.au3

@CR IE.au3 is a UDF (User Defined Function) library for the @CR AutoIt scripting language. @CR

@CR IE.au3 allows you to either create or attach to an Internet Explorer browser and do @CR just about anything you could do with it interactively with the mouse and @CR keyboard, but do it through script. @CR

@CR You can navigate to pages, click links, fill and submit forms etc. You can @CR also do things you cannot do interactively like change or rewrite page @CR content and JavaScripts, read, parse and save page content and monitor and act @CR upon browser 'events'.

@CR IE.au3 uses the COM interface in AutoIt to interact with the Internet Explorer @CR object model and the DOM (Document Object Model) supported by the browser. @CR

@CR Here are some links for more information and helpful tools:

IE.au3 is a UDF (User Defined Function) library for the
IE.au3 allows you to either create or attach to an Internet Explorer browser and do
just about anything you could do with it interactively with the mouse and
keyboard, but do it through script.
You can navigate to pages, click links, fill and submit forms etc. You can
also do things you cannot do interactively like change or rewrite page
content and JavaScripts, read, parse and save page content and monitor and act
IE.au3 uses the COM interface in AutoIt to interact with the Internet Explorer
object model and the DOM (Document Object Model) supported by the browser.
Here are some links for more information and helpful tools:
• AutoIt IE Builder (build IE scripts interactively)
• DebugBar (DOM inspector, HTTP inspector, HTML validator and more - free for personal use) Recommended
• IE Developer Toolbar (comprehensive DOM analysis tool)
• MODIV2 (view the DOM of a web page by mousing around)
• HTML Validator (verify HTML follows format rules)
